The Board and Management of the Federal Teaching Hospital, Ido-Ekiti (FETHI), Ekiti State, has rejoiced with the Muslim community in the hospital on the Eid-El-Kabir. A statement from the Information/Corporate Affairs Department urged the Muslim faithful in the hospital to imbibe the spirit of loyalty and commitment as exemplified by Prophet Ibrahim (A.S).   Why I selected Shettima as running mate, by Tinubu     Sickle cell sensitisation for students     Ex-Chief Judge decries inhabitation of borstal homes by…   It also admonished members of staff to draw lessons from Prophet Ibrahim’s examples by eschewing tendencies that could severe the unity and stability of the country. The management assured the public that the hospital will continue to give the best services and set the pace for their wellbeing.